[ProMED-mail thanks Dr Günther Slesak and colleagues for submission of their patient's findings. We wish the patient a more rapid and full recovery.

This patient visited the Dan Springs and the Jordan River National Park. The Dan Stream rises in the Tel Dan Nature Reserve -- the largest and most important of the sources of the Jordan River (https://en.parks.org.il/ParksAndReserves/teldan/Pages/default.aspx). Tel Dan Nature Reserve is in the northern Golan Heights (see map at https://goo.gl/maps/RdjwnYeUumN2). The Jordan River National Park, located about 50-60 km (31 to 37 mi) south of Tel Dan has walking trails that pass by water sources, aqueducts, pools, and sites of archaeological interest, such as the ancient Bethsaida (https://shalomisraeltours.com/jordan-river-national-park/, http://www.israeltripplanner.com/galilee-lake/nature-parks/jordan-park). - Mod.ML

